Which file sets the global or default values for the ssh command client behavior?
A)  /etc/ssh/config
B)  /etc/ssh/client_config
C)  /etc/ssh/ssh_config
D)  /etc/ssh/sshd_config
C
C. The file /etc/ssh/ssh_config contains default values for client behavior that canbe overridden by ~/.ssh/config values on a per- user basis. Of the other files, /etc/ssh/sshd_config is valid but defines server- related configuration.
